<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each loop is broken. Trace it, fix it, and explain <strong>why</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A — no turn.</strong> The four <code>if</code>/<code>elif</code> lines were deleted, so the direction never changes.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">for step in range(12):
    fill GOLD from (x, y, z) to (x + 2, y, z + 2)
    y = y + 1
    x = x + 4
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What shape do you get instead of a spiral, and why? Write the fix.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B — turn too small.</strong> A friend changed each turn to <code>+ 2</code> and <code>- 2</code>. It runs, but the four corners overlap into a blob.</p>
<p><strong>Each square is 3 wide. Explain why a turn of <code>+ 4</code> clears the last square but <code>+ 2</code> overlaps it.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

